<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Holds Ministerial-Level Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council
of the United Nations convened here today a ministerial-level
meeting on the subject of Africa.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at the conflict-resolution and development
in Africa. The result of the meeting will be a declaration
entitled "Presidential Declaration on Africa".
</P>
<P>
African issues that the Security Council has been concerned
about in the recent months include the situation in the Republic
of the Congo, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Sierra Leone,
Burundi, Rwanda, Somalia and the disputed territory of Western
Sahara.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be addressed first by the President of
Zimbabwe and Chairman of the Organization of African Unity Robert
Mugabe, and then the Secretary-General Kofi Annan will make a
speech followed by the Secretary-General of the Organization of
African Unity Salim Salim. After that, the ministers from the 15
members of the Security Council will address the meeting in
alphabetical order starting with Chile.
</P>
<P>
The permanent members of the Security Council are China,
France, Russian Federation, the United Kingdom and the United
States. The current non-permanent members of the Security Council
are Chile, Costa Rica, Egypt, Guinea-Bissau, Japan, Kenya, Poland,
Portugal, Republic of Korea and Sweden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
