<HEADLINE> Bomb Disposal Squad Rushes to Pak Explosion Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A bomb disposal squad from
the Pakistan Army has rushed to a tribal region, where about 30
people died Wednesday in an explosion, to clear all the remaining
explosives there, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 people were reportedly killed and dozens injured in
an explosion in an arms shop Wednesday evening in Bajaur, around
80 kilometers northwest of Peshawar, capital of Pakistan's North
West Frontier Province.
</P>
<P>
However, the cause of the explosion was not immediately known
and investigations were in progress, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The bomb disposal squad has gone there at the request of Bajaur
 to help clear the area around the shop, where a large quantity of
unexploded ammunition lies littered, to avoid any more damage to
human life and property, they said.
</P>
<P>
Being a semi-autonomous tribal region, Bajaur, inhabited mainly
by Pashtoons, enjoys a special status in Pakistan and is ruled
according to local traditions enforced by tribal chiefs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
