<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Cultural Spending Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The overall government
spending on culture fell for the sixth straight year in Canada in
1995/96, Statistics Canada said today.
</P>
<P>
The country's federal, provincial and municipal governments
spent a total of 5.82 billion Canada dollars (4.2 billion
U.S. dollars) on culture in fiscal 1995/96, 0.4 percent down from
the previous year, the national statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
Adjusted for inflation, the spending was down 1.3 percent from
the previous year, and 6.5 percent down from the peak in 1989/90,
it said.
</P>
<P>
Canada's cultural spending is primarily financed through
government appropriations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
