<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Scandinavian Countries Sign Aviation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI,September 25 (Xinhua) -- Agreements on air services
between Vietnam and three Scandinavian countries were signed here
today, Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The move marked the formal implementation of scheduled air
services cooperation between Vietnam and Sweden, Norway and Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The agreements cover areas including traffic rights,
designation of airlines, utilization of airports and facilities,
customs duties, storage of airborne equipment and supplies,
exchange of statistics, tariffs, transfer of earnings, airline
representation and aviation security.
</P>
<P>
They also specify the routes to be operated by the designated
airlines of Vietnam and those of the countries in the
international air services.
</P>
<P>
The agreements will facilitate economic, cultural, and
scientific and technical cooperation between them and meet
increasing needs for civil aviation, the VNA said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
