<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 16:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab League Condemns Renewed Turkish Troop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The 22-member Arab League today
condemned the renewed Turkish military incursion into Iraqi
territory early this week, calling for immediate withdrawal of
troops.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here, the Arab League Secretariat
denounced that the Turkish military action was carried out under
the false pretext of handling an internal problem inside the
territory of another country.
</P>
<P>
Such an action constitutes a flagrant violation of the
sovereignty and the territorial integrity of an AL member state,
and of international laws and the U.N. Charter, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement underlined the organization's resolve to
safeguard Iraq's sovereignty and territorial integrity, adding the
AL is following with the utmost concern the on-going Turkish
military operation.
</P>
<P>
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel has said that the objective
of the Turkish troop incursion into north Iraq is not to occupy
it, but to "clean" the region from the Kurdistan Workers Party
(PKK) bases.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting for autonomy in southeastern Turkey
since 1984. About 20,000 people have been killed ever since. The
PKK has bases in northern Iraq as Baghdad lost control of the
region after the Gulf War. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
