<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Russians Want to Retain Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Approximately 47 percent of
Russians hope that Chechnya would remain Russian territory, but
only 13 percent believe Russia must bring troops to the breakaway
republic and use force if relatons become totally hostile,
Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
A poll taken recently by the Public Opinion Foundation among
1,500 urban and rural dwellers suggests only some 41 percent of
Russians believe the best way to settle the Chechen problem is to
allow Chechnya to secede from the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
The poll also showed 31 percent of Russians continue to see the
North Caucasus republic as part of the federation, while 35
percent have begun to see it as an independent republic, the
Russian news service said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
