<HEADLINE> Hamas Accuses Israel of Attempting to Murder its </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- An official of the Hamas Amman
office said today that the office head, Khalid Mashiel, faced an
assassination attempt by Israel, but this was denied by Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Mohamad Nazal, official of the militant Palestinian movement
stationed in the Jordanian capital of Amman, said in a statement
faxed to Xinhua that two Canadians tried to kill Mashiel with an
electrical device this morning in front of his office.
</P>
<P>
the statement said the incident happened when Mashiel left his
car for the office, adding that his two security guards fought
back the Canadians.
</P>
<P>
The Hamas statement said one of the guards was injured and
later hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
It said that the incident was an assassination attempt
against Mashiel and that the Israeli security departments were
behind it.
</P>
<P>
But the statement said Hamas was not frightened by such
attempts and it would continue to fight its enemies.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian government, however, dismissed the incident as
merely a quarrel between the driver of Mashiel and two Canadian
tourists, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Minister of State for Information Affairs Samir
Mutawe told the press that Mashiel was not on the scene of the
incident at the time of the quarrel, during which Mashiel's driver
and the two Canadian tourists were wounded.
</P>
<P>
Mutawe said that Jordanian police detained those involved in
the quarrel, searched the tourists' car, but found no arms.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened amid increased Arab-Israeli tension here
triggered by an ambush against Israeli diplomats Monday outside
the Israeli embassy in Amman, during which two Israeli security
guards were wounded, and the attackers are still at large.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994 and is one of
the two Arab countries that have diplomatic relations with the
Jewish state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
