<HEADLINE> PNA Condemns Israeli Decision to Build More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) today strongly condemned the
Israeli government's plan of building more housing units in
Efrat, south of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The settlement expansion decided by the Israeli government may
lead to violence, Faisal Husseini, PNA Minister of Jerusalem
Affairs, was quoted as saying today by Jerusalem Media and
Communication Center (JMCC).
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Qureia, Speaker of the Palestinian Council, said in Gaza
today that "Netanyahu's declaration to build 300 new housing
units in Efrat is taking one more step to the killing of the
peace process."
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Wednesday night
that his government will continue to bolster the Jewish
settlements in the West bank and plans to build an additional 300
housing units for Jewish settlers in Efrat.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government today defended its settlement expansion
decision by saying that this plan was not made by the Netanyahu
government, but by the previous Labor government.
</P>
<P>
Salah Ta'amri, a Palestinian Council member elected from
Bethlehem, angrily told the Israeli Radio this evening that the
Netanyahu government is telling the lie. It is the Netanyahu
government that made the decision to build more housing units in
the West Bank, not the previous one, he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright also
criticized this plan, saying that she does not regard it as
consistent to the kind of climate for negotiations that she
wanted to create. 
</P>
</TEXT>
