<HEADLINE> Ireland pledges continued support for Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Irish delegation
pledged Ireland's continued support for Zambia, especially in the
civil service restructuring and social sector.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which is in Lusaka to attend the second annual
consultative meeting of the Zambia-Ireland bilateral cooperation,
reafirmed Ireland's commitment to supporting the country's
traditional sectors in water sanitation, primary education,
upgrading of unplanned settlements and improving primary health
care institutions.
</P>
<P>
A positive characteristic of the Irish aid has been the
involvement of local communities in the projects in its effort to
build local capacity and the capacity of the ownerships of the
programs, acting Zambian Finance Minister Peter Machungwa said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The programs have a common factor as they all assist the low
income groups to improve their life quality, Machungwa said.
</P>
<P>
Machungwa assured the delegation that the Zambian government
is committed to the restructuring of the civil service through
the public sector reform program.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also expressed Ireland's willingness to assist
Zambia in strengthening institutions related to human rights and
good governance. 
</P>
