<HEADLINE> Arab League Calls for Pressures on Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) today
called on the international community to extend backings to the
Palestinian people and pressurize Israel into ending its
violations of the signed peace agreements.
</P>
<P>
In a statement marking the anniversary of the Palestinian
Intifada (uprising), AL appealed to the United States, Russia, the
European Union, China, Japan and other peace-loving forces to
support the Palestinians' struggle for self determination and
establishment of an independent state with Jerusalem as its
capital.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians held demonstrations and general strikes on
September 25, 1996 to protest Israel's opening of a tunnel in East
Jerusalem with the pretext of exploiting for tourism.
</P>
<P>
AL said what Israel had done in Jerusalem violated the
Palestinian-Israeli agreements which stipulated that the status of
the city be discussed during the final phase of negotiations
between both sides.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the final phase of negotiations has become a
question with the peace process remaining deadlocked since last
March when Israel started the controversial Har Homa settlement
project in Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The AL's statement held Israel fully responsible for the grave
consequences of the practices for threatening the Arab nature,
Islamic and Christian characteristics of Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
