<HEADLINE> Muslim Congress to Launch Initiative on Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Muslim Congress
(WMC) will soon despatch a delegation to Afghanistan to buttress
the efforts of the United Nations to bring peace to the
war-shattered country.
</P>
<P>
The composition of the delegation will be decided within 10
days and "we have some impartial names in mind" who can help
handle the delicate Afghan situation, said WMC Secretary General
Zafar ul Haq at a press conference here today after the conclusion
of a three-day WMC conference.
</P>
<P>
Zafar said the WMC had contacted the Afghan Islamic Taliban
militia, who now control two thirds of the Afghan territory, and
their rival northern alliance, and "found there was a scope to
continue peace efforts."
</P>
<P>
The conference attended by delegates from 33 countries focused
on the specific problems of the Muslim countries.
</P>
<P>
The scholars and experts to the conference also debated on
issues including terrorism, drug trafficking, refugees and
juvenile delinquency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
