<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Brazilian Finance Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji,
meeting this afternoon with Brazilian Finance Minister Pedro
Sampaio Malan, said that China and Brazil have sound co-operation
in various areas, especially in trade and technology and that
China is ready to work for the promotion of bilateral trade and
economic co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Malan said that the World Bank has listed China and Brazil
among five countries that will make great progress in the next
century, and therefore the relationship between the two countries
is strategic.
</P>
<P>
Brazil hopes to increase its ties with China in trade, the
economy, culture, and aeronautics, he noted, and said he believes
that Brazilian-Chinese co-operation will grow in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the meeting was Xie Xuren, Chinese
Vice-minister of Finance.  
</P>
</TEXT>
