<HEADLINE> Chinese Armed Forces Called To Lead CPC Congress Spirit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese military leaders have
asked the armed forces to take the lead in implementing the
resolutions of the 15th National Congress of Communist Party of
China (CPC), and to maintain loyalty to the newly elected CPC
Central Committee headed by General Secretary Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of senior officers of the People's Liberation Army
today, Zhang Wannian, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee and vice chairman of the Central Military
Commission, said that high-ranking officers should set a good
example in implementing the resolution of the CPC Congress, and be
more steadfast in holding the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high.
</P>
<P>
He said that the armed forces must obey orders from the CPC
Central Committee and Central Military Commission without fail,
and safeguard the supreme authority the Party's third-generation
of leaders with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
He said the Congress' resolution on cutting 500,000 troops over
the next three years will help improve armed forces quality and
must be carried out to the letter.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, defense minister and vice chairman of the Central
Military Commission, also gave high marks to the Congress during a
visit to a tank division stationed near Beijing today, and said
that PLA officers and enlisted personnel should be armed with Deng
Xiaoping Theory and should keep in step with the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
China's armed forces will give full support to the country's
economic development and implement the Party's policies on
stepping up reforms, Chi said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
