<HEADLINE> European Commissioner to Visit Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 26 (Xinhua) -- European Commissioner Emma
Bonino will visit Afghanistan from September 28 to 30 to assess
the humanitarian situation in the war-torn country, the Delegation
of the European Commission to Pakistan said here today in a press
release.
</P>
<P>
Bonino, member of the European Community Humanitarian Office
(ECHO), is to assess the humanitarian situation in Afghanistan's
major cities including the capital of Kabul and to see ECHO funded
projects there, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
While in Pakistan, Bonino will meet with State Minister for
Foreign Affairs Siddique Khan Kanju and will contact with
representatives of U.N. agencies, international organizations and
non-governmental organizations, the release said.
</P>
<P>
ECHO has committed over 32 million ECU (about 35 million U.S.
dollars) of humanitarian aid for the Afghan people in 1997, the
release said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
