<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Treasury Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that he and US President Clinton will jointly set the
guidelines for Sino-US relations for the 21st century based on the
principles of the three Sino-US joint communiques.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is to meet with Clinton in the US in October. During a
meeting with US Treasury Secretary Robert Robin, Jiang said that
he expects to discuss a wide range of issues including Sino-US
relations and the international situation to push bilateral
relations into a new stage of healthy and steady development.
</P>
<P>
This is in the fundamental interest of the two countries'
people, he said, and beneficial to world peace, stability and
development. Present Sino-US relations are good, with high level
exchanges increasing, economic and trade ties developing steadily,
and co-operation and exchanges in other sectors expanding, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
"Sino-US relations are now facing a good opportunity of
further improvement and development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rubin is here as the head of a US delegation for the 10th
conference of the Sino-US Joint Economic Committee. The committee
was formed by Deng Xiaoping and former US President Jimmy Carter
in 1979, and has met for ten conferences, playing an active role
in mutual understanding and stimulating economic and trade
co-operation, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Communist Party of China (CPC) has just
concluded its 15th National Congress, which elected the new
leaders of the Central Committee, and made strategic arrangements
for China's trans-century development.
</P>
<P>
China's reforms and opening up have entered a new historical
stage, Jiang said, expressing confidence that the Chinese people
will advance the great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Rubin conveyed President Clinton's best regards to President
Jiang and congratulated the CPC on the successful conclusion of
the 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes the Party Congress will have a far-reaching
impact on China's reform, opening up and modernization drive in
the future.
</P>
<P>
He added that President Clinton is expecting President Jiang's
state visit to the US and the US side has a good reason to believe
that the visit will serve as a milestone for mature, solid and
stable Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
US and China have carried out mutually-beneficial co-operation
and exchanges in the economy, trade, and finance and will see new
progress in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin asked Rubin to convey his best regards to
President Clinton. enditem
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
