<HEADLINE> Muslim World Strives for UN Security Council Seat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 26 (Xinhua) -- World Muslim Congress (WMC)
called here today for a permanent seat in the U.N. Security
Council for the Muslim world.
</P>
<P>
Being about one fourth of humanity which has a global presence
and reach, the Muslim world "should strive unitedly for a
collective permanent seat in the Security Council of the United
Nations Organization," the WMC said in a declaration after the
conclusion of a three-day international conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference, "Muslim Ummah in the Next Century," deliberated
upon the various problems faced the Muslims all over the world.
</P>
<P>
"For too long has the Muslim Ummah been put on the defensive,
with international sanctions operating against some of its active
members," the declaration said.
</P>
<P>
"It is, about time that the Ummah asserted itself by reversing
the game and turning the tables on its adversaries," it said.
</P>
<P>
The Ummah, the declaration said, "needs to highlight and fight
for its just Islamic causes, collectively, by applying sanctions
against its aggressors and enemies."
</P>
<P>
"No unilateral dealings with the enemies should be permitted,
unless justice is assured," it added.
</P>
<P>
The declaration also called for the institution of an Islamic
Human Rights Commission as "some aggressive circles" in the west
mis-use the issue to interfere in the affairs of Muslim states.
</P>
</TEXT>
