<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 13:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fighting Desertification Under Way in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Crowning 10 years of
relentless efforts to fight desertification, Algeria has made
achievements in checking the rampant disaster across the country.
</P>
<P>
Algerian Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries said today
progress has been made in checking the spread of desertification
in about 84 percent of the total area of the country.
</P>
<P>
A so-called "Green Dam Project" has been implemented for
afforestation of a 1,200-kilometer tract extending from the
western end of the country eastwards.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian People's Army played an outstanding role in the
anti-desertification campaign. It undertook the afforestation of
some 108,000 hectares of pastoral desert lands and sand dunes.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the government has also been trying to raise
the awareness of the people and change their outlook toward nature
in an intensified campaign to bring desertification under control.
</P>
<P>
Algeria has 7.5 million hectares of arable land, a merely 3
percent of the country's total area. On the other hand, the
pastoral lands which are immediately threatened with
desertification amount to 8.7 million hectares, taking into
account that 40,000 hectares of agricultural land are annually
lost to sand invasions.
</P>
<P>
Algerian experts blamed torrents, wind and scarcity of water
for the worsening of environment, which led to drop in
agricultural production, shrinking of natural wealth and food, and
decline of fertility of the soil.
</P>
<P>
They call upon local Algerian authorities to earmark more funds
for projects to safeguard forests, expand afforestation and
protect them against fire. Meanwhile, they advise expediting
classification of forest trees to suit the particular
characteristics of the soil.
</P>
<P>
But the threat is still there. In order to effectively control
desertification, the Algerian government will have to undertake
tremendous and long-term actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
