<HEADLINE> Ramos Urges Greater Efforts for Government Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today urged the nation's leaders to redouble their efforts
during the last nine months of his term to attain the remaining
tasks on the government's economic, social and anti-poverty
agenda.
</P>
<P>
Ramos made the appeal to cabinet members, legislators,
representatives of the business community and leaders of other
sectors at the closing of a one-day national consultative
conference on socio-economic development at the Presidential
Palace.
</P>
<P>
"We must redouble our efforts to aggressively pursue the
government's remaining components of the economic, social and
anti-poverty agenda just as we strive to prepare our country and
people more competitively for the coming century," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said his administration had worked hard during the past
five years and the Filipino people are only beginning to taste the
benefits of the government's efforts.
</P>
<P>
During the remaining months of his term, apart from
consolidating the gains the government has achieved, "We must work
together to insure that they are not eroded, but instead, nurtured
to bear more fruits", he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking earlier at the opening ceremony of the conference,
Ramos called anew for greater unity, solidarity and team work
between the government and the citizenry to "weather the storm" in
the economy caused by recent speculative attacks on the peso and
other Southeast Asian currencies.
</P>
<P>
Ramos reminded the conference participants that it was "unity,
solidarity and teamwork" that had made the country economically
progressive and politically stable for the past five years.
</P>
