<HEADLINE> Thai Boxer Retains WBF Junior Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Samson Dutchboygym
retained his World Boxing Federation (WBF) junior bantamweight
title with a unanimous points decision over challenger Ges Marca
of the Philippines in Saraburi, Thailand on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The undefeated 25-year old won a tough fight to become the
first Thai champion to record 20 consecutive defences of his title.
</P>
<P>
Marca, 26, the fifth-ranked contender, scored with one-two
combinations to the face and guarded well, going the distance as
he did in Samson's 16th defence earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Despite his failure to match his usually impressive victories,
Samson was more accurate and his left hooks got through to the
head and the body.
</P>
<P>
Judges Martin Dalida (Philippines), Lertsin Dhamaniyom
(Thailand) and Ray Vickley (Australia) scored the fight 117-112,
119-112 and 119-111, respectively, all in favour of the champion.
</P>
<P>
Samson's record improved to 25 wins (22 KOs), while Marca's
became 33 wins (17 KOs), three draws and 10 losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
