<HEADLINE> Eritrean President Visits Egypt Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Eritrean President Asaias
Afworki will start a two-day visit here tomorrow to hold talks with
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak with a view to enhancing bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the fourth since 1993, Afworki is to hold
consultations with Mubarak on bilateral, regional and
international questions and coordinate stances on a number of
issues, the Middle East News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Afworki-Mubarak talks will specifically cover the
Yemen-Eritrean dispute over the Hanish Islands, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The Red Sea island of Greater Hanish, which the Eritreans now
controls, is one of three islands claimed by Yemen and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The two sides pledged to refrain from any action or military
operation until the ruling by an arbitration court is made under
the Yemen-Eritrea Arbitration Agreement signed in Paris in October
last year.
</P>
<P>
As for bilateral ties, the two sides will endeavor to overcome
"some obstacles," the MENA said without elaborating. It said
Eritrea is interested in making use of Egypt's experience in
implementing its economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
Egypt was the first state to officially recognize Eritrea's
independence after 30 years of struggle on May 25, 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
