<HEADLINE> Singapore Sends Experts to Indonesia to Tackle Haze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has sent three
environment and weather experts to Indonesia to help tackle the
current haze problem, the Environment Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
It said that the three experts, who left here for Jakarta,
capital of Indonesia, on Thursday evening, were sent at the
request of the Indonesia state minister of environment and will
find out what technical expertise, equipment and training are
needed there.
</P>
<P>
The experts are now at the Command Post at the Environmental
Impact Management Agency in Jakarta to help Indonesian officials
monitor the situation, the ministry said, adding that two other
experts will be posted there for the duration of the haze.
</P>
<P>
The smog caused by fires in Indonesia remained relatively
stable in Singapore in the last two days, with the Pollutant
Standard Index staying most of the time below the 100 mark level,
or within the healthy range.  
</P>
