<HEADLINE> China's Confucian Culture Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 International
Confucian Culture Festival opened today in Shandong province,
commemorating the 2,548th anniversary of the birth of Confucius
(551-479 BC).
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 people from 20 countries and regions were
present at the opening ceremony, including the Swedish Ambassador
to China Sven Linder, the Austrian Ambassador to China Dr. Gerhard
Ziegler, and Kong Demao, a 77th generation descendant of Confucius.
</P>
<P>
The 15-day festival will have Confucian dances and music,
exhibitions of painting and calligraphy, cultural relics, and
seminars on Confucius and Confucianism in Qufu City, his hometown.
</P>
<P>
It is sponsored by the Shangdong Provincial Tourism Bureau and
the city governments of Jining and Qufu and is an international
festival designated by the National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, nearby Jining has developed tourism rapidly
along with its economy, said Wang Renyuan, the mayor. There are
750 foreign-funded enterprises in Jining, with 500 million US
dollars in foreign funds. The city had 5.5 million tourists last
year, 50,000 from abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
