<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Drug Trafficker Gets Death Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- A drug trafficker was
sentenced to death today by an Indian sessions court in Haryana
State near New Delhi, official sources said here.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in India that a death penalty was given
for narcotics trafficking offense.
</P>
<P>
The court judge ordered the death sentence to Neki Ram, 55, for
repeated drug trafficking. Ram was earlier sentenced to 10 years
of rigorous imprisonment for carrying 10 kilograms of opium and
800 grams of charas in 1988. He was caught with 15 kilograms of
opium and 300 grams of charas while on bail in the first case.
</P>
<P>
The court in its order said that drug trafficking was not only
an economic offense but also considered often as "subtle murder"
practiced on the community.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970926.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
