rewarding and useful."
During his stay in New York, Gujral held talks with U.S.
President Bill Clinton on bilateral relations and regional
situation. Clinton supported the Indo-Pakistani dialogue aiming to
improve their ties. Gujral also met in New York his Pakistani
counterpart Nawaz Sharif for the second time this year. The two,
who had met in mid May, exchanged views on bilateral relations.
</P>
