<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sleeping Sickness Occurs in Mozmabique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- At least seven to 15
Mozambicans suffer from deadly sleeping sickness, with 75-80
percent of the cases occurringns in northern Tete and Niassa
provinces every year, the Noticias paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Director of the National Health Bureau
Martinho Dgedge yesterday, who said that proper measures must be
taken to prevent the disease which threatens lives of human
beings and animals from spreading.
</P>
<P>
He also said that his bureau will formulate an investigation
plan to determine areas plagued by sleeping sickness and the
National Bureau of Animal Husbandry will take the responsibility
to monitor and eradicate tsetse flies which disseminate the
disease.
</P>
<P>
Zambia, Tanzania, Malawi and Mozambique are infected with
sleeping sickness as tsetse flies are often seen in these four
southern African countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
