<HEADLINE> China, Kazakhstan to Promote Bilateral Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said today Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing's visit to
Kazakhstan would further improve mutual trust and close ties
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting, Nazarbayev praised the report delivered by
Chinese President Jiang Zemin at the 15th National Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party, especially the Chinese policy of keeping
friendly neighborhood, opposing hegemonism and safeguarding world
peace.
</P>
<P>
He said that Kazakhstan and China, both facing the task of
development, need long-term peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the two countries would further strengthen
their good-neighborly, equal and mutually-beneficial relations
geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev added that following Premier Li Peng's visit to
Kazakhstan on September 24-25, more cooperation projects were
proposed during Li Lanqing's visit.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here on September 24 for an official visit to
Kazakhstan, said that Sino-Kazakh economic and trade cooperation
has developed well with the bilateral trade volume increasing year
by year.
</P>
<P>
He said China would continue to support and encourage
enterprises of both sides to establish direct economic and
technological cooperation and mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Nazarbayev and Li attended the signing
ceremony of a customs cooperation agreement and a contract on the
establishment of a joint oil and gas stock company. 
</P>
