<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Lays Wreath at French Memorial Plaque in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting French President
Jacques Chirac laid a wreath Thursday at the memorial plaque here,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The memorial plaque features the names of 42 French volunteers,
who created the Normandy-Neman Air Regiment in the Soviet
Union. During World War II, the unit flew a total of 5,240 combat
missions, participated in 869 air fightings and brought down or
damaged 80 Nazi planes.
</P>
<P>
Chirac, who arrived here Wednesday for a three-day state visit
to Russia, was one of the first Western leaders who visited Russia
after August 1991.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting with Chirac on Wednesday, Russian President
Boris Yeltsin said that "Russian-French cooperation has risen to
the level of privileged partnership".
</P>
<P>
He lauded Chirac's contribution to the transformation of the
Group 7 into the Group 8, which included Russia. He also praised
Chirac's efforts in Russia-NATO rapprochement and Russia's joining
in the Paris Club.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is expected to hold talks with Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin today on the work of the Russian-French
inter-government commission for economic and scientific and
technical cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
