<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PNA Shuts Down 17 Hamas Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) has shut down 17 Islamic Resistance Movement
(Hamas) institutions in the self-rule areas to exhibit its
determination to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported today that 16 Hamas-run charities in the
Gaza Strip were closed by Palestinian police, including a
kindergarten, a sport club and a girl school. And a
Hamas-affiliated Television Station was sealed off in the West
Bank city of Nablus.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, PNA security forces continued their round up of
Hamas activists. About 200 Hamas and Islamic Jihad members have
been detained in the Palestinian-controlled territories over the
past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
PNA's crackdown on Hamas institutions and its activists came
after Israeli security officials presented evidence that
identified four out of five suicide bombers in Jerusalem attacks
as Palestinians from the West Bank, not from abroad as PNA has
insisted.
</P>
<P>
According to Israel's General Security Service, the four who
blew themselves up in Jerusalem's Mahane Yehuda market on July 30
and the Ben Yehuda pedestrian mall on September 4, killing 20
Israelis and wounding hundreds, were all residents of Azira
Shamalya, a Palestinian village near Nablus under Israeli security
control.
</P>
<P>
The fifth bomber has not been identified, but is believed to be
Mahmoud Abu Hanude from the same village, the alleged recruiter
and ringleader of the suicide squads.
</P>
<P>
As PNA security forces continued their arrests, Israeli troops
were kept at a high state of alert for fear of more terror
attacks. Israeli security officials claimed that the risk of
further attacks remained as long as PNA left the Hamas
infrastructure intact.
</P>
<P>
However, PNA President Yasser Arafat told reporters that he was
making a 100 percent effort to crack down on terrorists. He denied
responsibility for the suicide bombings, noting that the bombers
came from Area B, where Israel continues to have security
control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
