<HEADLINE> 114 Ugandans Released in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Among 208 Ugandans arrested
recently in Kenya, 114 have been released since the Ugandan
Foreign Ministry intervened, a senior official has said.
</P>
<P>
Rebecca Kadaga, the state minister in Foreign Ministry in
charge of regional cooperation, told "The New Vision" that the
relations between Uganda and Kenya are good.
</P>
<P>
The remained 94 other arrested Ugandans reportedly have no
valid documents or have expired documents. The state minister
said she doubted if they are all Ugandan civilians.
</P>
<P>
The Parliamentary Committee on Foreign Affairs was disturbed
by the reports that some Ugandans have been beheaded recently in
Nairobi. The committee asked Kenya to guarantee the security of
Ugandans in Kenya on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan high commissioner in Kampala could not be contacted for
comment on the matter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
