<HEADLINE> Senior Party Official Meets Venezuelan Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, met here today with a delegation
from the Venezuelan Christian Socialist Party led by its vice
president Jose Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that although China is in the Eastern Hemisphere and
Venezuela in the Western Hemisphere, their peoples enjoy a
time-honored friendship.
</P>
<P>
He noted that bilateral relations have developed steadily since
the forging of diplomatic relations in 1974, and that China thanks
Venezuela for its support on the issues of Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed the Venezuelan visitors on the 15th CPC
National Congress, saying that the most conspicuous achievement of
the congress is the establishment of Deng Xiaoping Theory as the
guiding ideology of the CPC, and the formulation of the platform
of action for China's trans-century development under the guidance
of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The CPC and 1.2 billion Chinese people will steadfastly
continue to march along the path of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics set forth by Deng Xiaoping, he said.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez extended his congratulations on the successful
convening of the 15th CPC national congress, and on the reelection
of Jiang Zemin as general secretary of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has made great progress in its reform and
opening-up drive, and accumulated a wealth of experience which
Venezuela finds appealing.
</P>
<P>
He noted that his party is ready to further reinforce its
relations with the CPC so as to enhance mutual understanding and
promote friendly relations between the two countries and their
peoples.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, attended the meeting. Yesterday, Dai held
working talks with the delegation members,
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan visitors arrived here Thursday for a goodwill
visit to China. Apart from Beijing, they will travel to Shanghai,
Suzhou and Changsha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
