<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Approves 55 Investment Projects Since </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Export Processing
Zone Authority (EPZA) has approved over 55 projects since April
this year, Deputy Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Industry
and Commerce Owen Tshabangu said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing participants at the Scholastica 97 Conference
Thursday, Tshabangu said this had brought investment of more than
two billion Zimbabwe Dollars (less than 200 million U.S. Dollars)
while creating over 3,000 jobs.
</P>
<P>
He further said the projects were distributed throughout the
country and included manufacturing, processing of agricultural
commodities, food packaging and chemical production.
</P>
<P>
Introduced in 1994, the EPZA program was designed to promote
duty free exports and lure investment into the country. 
</P>
