<HEADLINE> People Bid Farewell to Jing Puchun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- State leaders and some 1,000
Chinese and foreign dignitaries gathered here today to bid
farewell to Jing Puchun, wife of the late Liao Chengzhi, former
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Jing died in Beijing on September 20 at the age of 80.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin; Premier Li Peng; Vice-Premier
Zhu Rongji; Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee; and Vice-President Rong Yiren sent wreaths to the
funeral ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, General Liu Huaqing, NPC Standing Committee
Vice-Chairman Cheng Siyuan; several vice-chairmen of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC); and other senior officials attended the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee-hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), and Anson Chan, chief secretary for
the Administration of the HKSAR government also sent wreaths.
</P>
<P>
Jing Puchun was born in Shangyu County, east China's Zhejiang
province, on April 17, 1917.
</P>
<P>
Jing, who joined the CPC in 1954, devoted herself to work for
overseas Chinese following the founding of the People's Republic
in 1949. She served as member of the CPPCC National Committee,
member of the Executive Committee of the All-China Women's
Federation and council member of the Sino-Japanese Friendship
Association.  
</P>
