<HEADLINE> Liaoning to Promote Cooperation with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Guo Tingbiao, deputy governor
of northeast China's Liaoning Province, said recently that the
province will adopt measures to increase cooperation with the Hong
Kong financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Guo told participants in a recent seminar on the province's
industrial restructuring effort that it is very important for
Liaoning to join hands with Hong Kong to upgrade the economy.
</P>
<P>
The province, one of China's key industrial bases, is home to
nearly one-third of the country's medium to large state-owned
enterprises, the vast majority of which have long been in
the red.
</P>
<P>
"Concrete steps will be taken to increase the number of
cooperation projects jointly funded by investors from the two
sides," said Guo, adding that Liaoning welcomes more Hong Kong
banks and insurance companies to open branches and offices his
province.
</P>
<P>
Guo noted that more local state-owned enterprises will
issue H shares on the Hong Kong stock market.
</P>
<P>
The province will also encourage Hong Kong securities
companies and stock traders to participate in local economic
undertakings, and will improve ties between the Shenyang Stock
Exchange and the Hong Kong Federation of Stock Exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Guo said Liaoning will provide more business opportunities to
Hong Kong investors in the coming years. He noted that the special
administrative region will in turn benefit from the province's
rapid economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
