<HEADLINE> WFP Officials Visit Recipient Areas in Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- World Food Program (WFP)
officials have wrapped up a two-day visit to Haidong Prefecture in
northwest China's Qinghai Province, where 300,000 poor people have
got rid of poverty because of WFP-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
As one of the poorest areas in China, Qinghai still has 676,000
impoverished people, accounting for 22 percent of its rural
population. It has completed two comprehensive agricultural
projects with funding offered by the WFP since 1985. A contract on
the third project was signed recently.
</P>
<P>
The previous two projects covered a wide range of fields
including water conservancy, village road construction,
afforestation and agro-technique training. The third is geared to
women and ethnic minorities.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day tour, WFP officials made house-to-house
stops in Huangzhong, Ping'an and Hualong counties and asked about
the changes which have taken place in the lives of the local
people.
</P>
<P>
Liu Guang, vice governor of Qinghai, said these projects have
produced praiseworthy results and become a model of comprehensive
agricultural development in Qinghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
