<HEADLINE> East Africa to Coop in AIDS Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- A three-day meeting of
senior health officials from Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda has
recommended that a task force be formed by next February to
specify areas of cooperation in AIDS control.
</P>
<P>
According to a report available here today from Arusha in the
north where the meeting ended Thursday, the task force will
examine national policies, research activities, including
clinical trial of drugs and vaccines, and factors influencing HIV
transmissions.
</P>
<P>
On the control of communicable diseases and epidemics, the
meeting called for a task force, also to be in place by next
February to address research, provision of drugs and vaccines,
advocacy and networking on disease surveillance and sourcing of
funds.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the first in the health sector under the auspices
of the East African Cooperation, urged re-establishment of links
in health research in the sub-region. 
