<HEADLINE> Uganda's Entebbe Zoo to Be Transformed into Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's Entebbe Zoo has
been undergoing transformation from a zoo to a semi-natural park,
reported local daily "The New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Yafes Otim-Omara, the state Minister for Tourism, Wildlife and
Antiquities, was quoted as saying that the zoo called the Uganda
Wildlife Education Center will be developed into both a focal
point for eco-tourism and a natural education resource in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Omara made the remarks on Thursday at an open day organized by
the center to commemorate the World Tourism Day which falls on
September 27.
</P>
<P>
He said the center is to become a nature-based tourism
attraction where wildlife could be seen in its natural
environment far different from a zoo.
</P>
<P>
The center attracted over 100,000 visitors last year and will
increase tremendously this year, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Omara said the government places a high priority on the
successful development of the center which is expected to play a
pivotal role in respect of both tourism development and
environmental education. 
</P>
