<HEADLINE> Chinese Delegation Leaves for Asia-Europe Economic Ministers' Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese government
delegation, led by Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Wu Yi, left here this morning for Japan to attend the
first Asia-Europe economic ministers' meeting under the
Asia-Europe Meeting.
</P>
<P>
This is the first meeting for Asia-Europe economic ministers
since the Asia-Europe Meeting held in March last year. The two-day
meeting is scheduled to open tomorrow in Makuhari of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Topics of discussion at the meeting include Asia-Europe
economic relations in general, trade and investment, business
exchanges, infrastructural construction, and sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also exchange views on the relations between
Asia-Europe Meeting and the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Wu is to deliver a keynote speech on
Asia-Europe trade and investment, and elaborate on the Chinese
government's position on strengthening economic and trade
cooperation between Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Wu will also meet with some economic ministers.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will receive delegations from 25 countries from the
European Union and Asia.
</P>
<P>
A report on the talks will be submitted to the second
Asia-Europe Meeting scheduled for next April in London. 
</P>
