<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Audit Foreign Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Labor Ministry and
the Ministry for Home Affairs will liaise in a crack-down to seek
out and expel foreign individuals working in the country without
proper residence and work permits.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Sebastian Kinyondo, Minister for Labor
and Youth Development, to the local press here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A nation-wide operation will be launched next month to audit
expatriate workers in the country, according to Kinyondo.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the employers will be required to furnish the
inspectors with particulars on the expatriates' terms of
employment and program for training Tanzanians to replace the
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Expatriates must strictly be engaged in the jobs specified in
their working permits and their qualifications should conform to
work assigned, Kinyondo said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that persons caught under the crack-down will be
expelled from the country, starting early next month. 
</P>
