<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bohai Rim Leads North China in Containers Transportation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's
biggest center for collection and distribution of international
container cargo broke ground in Tianjin Port early this month.
</P>
<P>
The 300,000-sq-m center, which is jointly financed by Tianjin,
the New World Group, the Anderson Group of Hong Kong with an
investment of 30 million US dollars, will be able to dispatch
newly-arrived containers to interior areas and other northeastern
areas of China.
</P>
<P>
As a result of China's rapid economic growth, Bohai Rim has
become a major container collection and distribution of in north
China, with a combined annual handling capacity of two million TEU.
</P>
<P>
Peng Tianyu, an expert on coastal planning, predicts that by
early next century, China's interior area will be blessed with a
container shipping network consisting of Tianjin, Dalian and
Qingdao ports in the north, Shanghai, Ningbo ports in the middle
and Yantian Port in the south.
</P>
<P>
Bohai Rim will become the biggest center for shipping of
containers in north China, Peng said.
</P>
<P>
Bohai Rim, located on the western bank of the Pacific Ocean,
near Russia to the north and the Korean Peninsula and Japan to the
east, is integral to the increasingly active northeastern Asian
economic area and one of the starting points for the Eurasian
Continental Bridge in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970926.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bohai Rim Leads North China in Containers Transportation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bohai Rim is composed of Liaoning, Hebei and Shandong
provinces, as well as Beijing and Tianjin municipalities. The
region contributes a quarter of both China's gross economic volume
and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The emergence of the container network is not only the product
of north China's foreign trade development and opening-up to the
outside world, but also indicates that Bohai Rim has become the
third-largest economic powerhouse in China after the southern and
eastern areas of the country.
</P>
<P>
Reports from major ports of entry in the Bohai Rim show that
about ten ports have been building or expanding berths, aiming to
develop container transport into a priority for port construction in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Port, the largest foreign trade outlet in north China,
has the biggest container berth in the country and has handled the
fifth-generation container ships since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao, China's third largest port for container shipping, is
building three new container berths in addition to its current
three container docks. Dalian Port, with the newly-built deepwater
berth of Dayao Bay, will have the best development potential of
any sea outlet in the Bohai Rim.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970926.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bohai Rim Leads North China in Containers Transportation (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways and the Tianjin Bonded Area have
jointly constructed two special railway lines which can quickly
send just-arrived container goods to northern, central,
northwestern and southwestern areas of China, starting the
country's first thoroughfare for the unified transportation of the
marine routes and railway lines and providing customers in major
Chinese cities with door-to-door service.
</P>
<P>
Wu Tao, Manager of Huatie Longtai Company which oversees the
business said that Mongolia has used Tianjin Port as their sea
route, and most of the cargo sent to Mongolia from the United
States, the Republic of Korea and Japan, is dispatched from
Tianjin Port. The unified shipping-railway-line network from
Tianjin Port handled 8,000 TEU of containers for Mongolia last
year.
</P>
<P>
To better balance the development of China's eastern and
western areas, 11 provinces and autonomous regions along the
Yellow River recently financed a company to import 50 large
container trucks specially for handling import and export
businesses for these areas. In Hebei Province alone, more than 20
companies are engaged in container transport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
