<HEADLINE> China to Maintain Cooperation with Rio Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China is willing to
maintain long-term and stable cooperation with the Rio Group, the
regional organization of Latin America, Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
He told foreign ministers from the Rio Group at
U.N. headquarters that China and Latin America are mutually
trustworthy friends.
</P>
<P>
Friendly relations between China and the Rio Group in various
fields is progressing smoothly and contacts between the two sides
are increasing, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
He added that there exists an even brighter future for their
greater cooperation in economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is also China's foreign minister, praised the Rio
Group's role in safeguarding stability, promoting economy and
pushing forward with regional integration in Latin America and the
Caribbean region.
</P>
<P>
Ruben Melgarejo Lanzoni, foreign minister of Paraguay, the
rotating coordinating state of the Group this year, said the Rio
Group values its regular dialogues with China.
</P>
<P>
Through the dialogues the two sides can discuss bilateral
relations as well as regional and international issues covering
economic and social development, environmental protection and the
elimination of illegal drugs.
</P>
<P>
Such dialogues are of vital importance to the growth of
cooperative relations between the group's member states and
China, Lanzoni said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also briefed each other on developments in their
respective nations and regions.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers from the group congratulated the
Communist Party of China on the conclusion of the 15th National
Congress, and Hong Kong's return to the motherland in July.
</P>
<P>
They said these events would have a positive impact on the
promotion of bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides, in addition, exchanged views on the reform of
the U.N. and other international issues of common concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
