<HEADLINE> Over 40 Drowned in India Bus Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 40 passengers
were feared drowned early today when a bus carrying them plunged
into a river in India's southern state of Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
The bus with 47 persons aboard was crossing a bridge while it
fell into the rain-swollen Krishna river at 1.15 a.m. local time
(1945 GMT Thursday), said reports reaching here from Hyderabad, the
state capital.
</P>
<P>
Only three people had managed to swim to safety, a state
transport official said. 
</P>
