<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 44 Dengue Cases Registered in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- With seven more dengue
cases reported in Indian Capital New Delhi, the total number of
dengue patients in the city has risen to 44, a local newspaper
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Earlier a death has already been reported in a private nursing
home in the capital. The dengue disease claimed over 500 lives in
the city last year.
</P>
<P>
Doctors have warned people not to take any fever case lightly
and immediately consult a medical practitioner. They said that if
there is delay in taking the patient to the doctor, then internal
bleeding might set in. This can prove dangerous for the patient.
</P>
<P>
Till now no medicine or vaccine is available for dengue
treatment. Scientists said that developing such a vaccine was
difficult as the disease was caused by different viral strains.
</P>
</TEXT>
