<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Police Seize 500 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian police
seized 500 kilograms of cocaine on the sea to the north
of Panama Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said today that anti-drug policemen sighted two
suspected speedboats during a routine patrol on the sea off an
island in the Colon province.
</P>
<P>
The policemen stopped the speedboats and exchanged fire with
three suspected drug traffickers who abandoned their boats later
and escaped.
</P>
<P>
On one of the speedboats, the policemen found 500 packages of
cocaine, which weighes one kilogram each.
</P>
<P>
Police believed that this lot of cocaine was related with what
they got in the last seizure because all of them were packed with
the "White Dolphin" trademark.
</P>
<P>
Police said that cocaine is sold at 5,000 U.S. dollars per
kilogram on the Panamanian market while on the international
market the price doubles.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian police have seized a total of 6,000 kilograms of
cocaine since the beginning of this year, of which 2,000 kilograms
were found in the Colon province alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
