<DOCNO> XIE19970926.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tax Revenue up in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's tax revenues between
January and August increased by 51.2 percent over the same period
last year, the national tax revenue agency said in a report
published today.
</P>
<P>
Net revenues for the period rose to 894.5 million U.S. dollars
from 591.7 million dollars collected in the same period of
1996. The added value tax and taxes for special consuming
registered an even larger increase.
</P>
<P>
Added value tax collection grew 54.3 percent to 458.8 million
dollars, against 297.4 million dollars in the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Special consuming tax revenue increased by 102.5 percent, which
amounted to 96.2 million dollars, against 47.5 million dollars
during the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Income tax revenue revealed a growing trend that produces
optimism in the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Income tax collection for the period grew 29.8 percent to 260.4
million dollars from the 215.2 million dollars received in the
same period of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
