<HEADLINE> Ruins of Ancient Manor Unearthed in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Italian archaeologists excavated
the ruins of a large-scale ancient manor in the suburb of Lucca
in central Italy.
</P>
<P>
The manor, which covers a floor space of some 800 square
meters, is believed to follow the design of structures built
during the Roman Empire.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists believe the manor may have been a wine-making
house in ancient Rome because they have unearthed a large brewing
vat from the ruins.
</P>
<P>
The excavation is still going on. Archaeologists say the manor
will provide information for studies on agricultural and social
systems of ancient Rome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
