<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Produces Pesticides from Medicinal Herbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- A local private company in
east China's Shandong province has developed a pesticide from
Chinese medicinal herbs, advertising the product as non-toxic and
environmentally-friendly.
</P>
<P>
The company has been given a patent for the pesticide, which
can be widely applied to kill pests harmful to vegetables,
flowers, trees, cotton and other crops,
</P>
<P>
The pesticide is not harmful to human beings, and can be called
a kind of "green pesticide," according to the local agricultural
administration authority.  
</P>
