<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Technical Assistance Grant to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has agreed to provide Nepal with a technical assistance
(TA) grant of 400,000 U.S. dollars for supporting its Agriculture
Statistics Development.
</P>
<P>
The TA will assist Nepal's Central Bureau of Statistics (CBS)
in institutionalizing a system of agriculture surveys that will
render reliable, timely and relevant statistics and minimize date
gaps, said a press release distributed by the ADB.
</P>
<P>
And the TA will help enhance the administrative and technical
capability of the CBS through personnel training, and help
implement a partially decentralized and more efficient data
processing system through the provision of consulting services and
some computing equipment, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB is among the Nepal Aid Group, which also includes the
World Bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
