<HEADLINE> Thai Former MP Gets Death Sentence for Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 26 (Xinhua) - Thavi Phutthachan, a former
member of parliament, has been sentenced to death for the murder
of Saengchai Sunthornwat, director of the Mass Communications
Organization of Thailand (MCOT), the Bangkok Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
Thavi faced three murder charges for hiring four gunmen to
assassinate Saengchai.
</P>
