<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Rises in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in the
Philippines in July 1997 rose to 8.7 percent from 7.5 percent last
year, according to data from the National Statistics Office today.
</P>
<P>
The number of unemployed persons increased by 17.2 percent from
2.2 million last year to 2.6 million in July this year.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 30.2 million persons joined the labor force in
July 1997, increasing by 497,000 or 1.7 percent over 29.7 million
last year.
</P>
<P>
Total employment summed up to 27.5 million, slightly up by 0.4
percent over last year, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
The number of underemployed persons in July 1997 increased by
7.5 percent, from 5.9 million last year to 6.3 million, the data
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
