<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 26 (Xinhua) - An earthquake shook Umbria in
central Italy early this morning and tremors were felt in the
Italian capital.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, the center of which lies to the north of the
Foligno city, was measured around 4.85 on the Richter scale,
Italy's National Geophysical Institute said.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known if the quake has caused any
casualties.
</P>
