<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold Mid-Year Gems Emporium in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar Mine Authorities
have announced that the Mid-Year Gems Emporium will be held here
on October 21-27.
</P>
<P>
Jade, gems and jewelry from local merchants will also put on
sale at the emporium in addition to those from the state-run
Myanmar Gems Enterprise, the New Light of Myanmar newspaper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The state-sponsored Myanmar gems emporiums have been held since
1964 with additional mid-year ones introduced in the past five
years.
</P>
<P>
The March emporium attracted more than 300 gems merchants from
16 countries and regions as well as more than 1,000 local gems
traders.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, Myanmar has earned a total of
250 million U.S. dollars from the 34 gems emporiums and five
mid-year ones.
</P>
<P>
The first Myanmar private gems fair sponsored by local private
companies was held here two weeks ago, displaying jewelry and
artifacts manufactured by the private sector.  
</P>
