<HEADLINE> Greece Olympiakos Gains Second Straight Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Champions Olympiakos of Greece
clinched their second straight EuroLeague basketball victory by
beating Russea's CSKA Moscow 86-74 here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The match was a one-side affair with the Greeks leading by an
average 10 points. Only in the closing minutes of the first half
Russian guard Igor Goudelin, who top scored with 26 points, shot
three straight triples, gaving CSKA a 43-42 halftime lead.
</P>
