<HEADLINE> First Collected Works of Living Chinese Philosopher Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The first collected works
of a living Chinese philosopher since the establishment of the
People's Republic of China in 1949 has been published.
</P>
<P>
"Gao Qinghai Collected Works of Philosophy," published by the
Jilin People's Publishing House in northeast China, contains the
bulk of the author's research achievements over the past several
decades.
</P>
<P>
Gao Qinghai, a well-known Chinese philosopher and professor in
Jilin University, has been studying the key issues
of modern-day philosophy, especially those related to China's
reforms and opening-up and socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
He has put forward many original ideas which have attracted the
attention of China's academic circle.
</P>
<P>
The two-million-character book is one of the important academic
achievements scored in study of philosophy in modern China,
experts here say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
