<HEADLINE> Hungary, Poland, Czech Republic Talk Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Hungary, Poland and the
Czech Republic today held talks on trilateral military cooperation
in the Hungarian city of Balatonkenese, 80 kilometers southwest of
Budapest.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian National Defense Forces Chief of General Staff
Vegh Ferenc and his Czech and Polish counterparts, Jiri Nekovasil
and Henryk Szumski, attended the meeting, the Hungarian Telegraph
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs reviewed the developments and circumstances
following the NATO Madrid summit, discussed their present military
status and decided upon specific areas in which the three
countries should cooperate during the process of entering NATO.
</P>
<P>
They agreed unanimously that it was also important for them to
cooperate with other Eastern European countries.
</P>
<P>
The talks were reportedly the first between the three chiefs;
the second discussion is scheduled for Prague in January, 1998.
</P>
