<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province to Strengthen Cooperation with Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, an
important industrial base in northeast China, will expand its
cooperation with Japan.
</P>
<P>
Wen Shixiong, governor of Liaoning, said during his meeting
with a visiting Japanese delegation recently that the cooperation,
which will benefit both sides, is to focus on machine-building,
metallurgical, petrochemical and electronics fields in his province.
</P>
<P>
He believed that his province is an attraction to Japan in
geological position, natural resources, technological forces,
industrial foundation and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Wen said his province has been regarding Japan as one of its
major partners, and will promote cooperation with Japan at both
official and non-government levels.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed Japanese enterprises, especially big enterprise
groups to invest in Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
The governor said the two sides can probe cooperation in
trade, electronics information, biological engineering, new
materials and other high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Wen said Liaoning has decided to introduce high technology and
high-tech equipment to upgrade its traditional industries.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested cooperation with Japan in research of
environmental protection strategy and industry, as well as
cooperation in agricultural and marine products development.
</P>
