<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspected Italian Mafia Boss Arrested in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 25 (Xinhua) - Spanish police announced today
that they have arrested a suspected top Italian mafia gangster in
the Spanish southern resort town of Huelva.
</P>
<P>
Police said they raided Rocco Piscioneri's villa and seized
jewelry, two luxury cars, mobile phones and an undetermined amount
of cash.
</P>
<P>
Piscioneri, who was on Interpol's wanted list, allegedly ran
the drug-arm of the Spanish "Ndrangheta" mafia. He was arrested as
part of a joint operation between Spanish and Italian authorities.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Spanish police also arrested 25 mafia suspects from
the Piscioneri organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
