<HEADLINE> China to be Giant in Technology: Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- China will become a leading
science power in the 21st century when science and technology play
a dominant role in people's lives, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
"By the middle of the next century, I believe, China will
become a science and technology giant in the world," said C N
Yang, a world-renowned physician and Nobel Prize winner in a
speech at Zhejiang University.
</P>
<P>
The professor from State University of New York at Stony Brook
was attending the Qiushi Science and Technology Foundation Award
Ceremony at Zhejiang University in this capital of East China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to more than 200 scholars from home and abroad,
Yang outlined the history of China's science and technology
development and its future prospects.
</P>
<P>
As a member of the advisory committee of Qiushi Science and
Technology foundation, Yang said he was especially impressed by
young prize winners under the age of 45.
</P>
<P>
These 37 scientists were selected from thousands of candidates
by the advisory committee consisting of five world-renowned
scientists. The panel included mathematician Chern Shing-shen,
physicians C N Yang and Zhou Guangzhao, chemist Yuan-Tseh Lee, and
medical expert Kan Yuet Wai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
