<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi of China Uses World Bank Loan in Planting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region will use a World Bank loan to help local
poverty-stricken people plant fast-growing trees.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi will use the 330 million yuan to plant pine, China fir,
eucalyptus, lichee and longan on 60,000 ha. of land in Hechi,
Liuzhou and Baise to help poor farmers escape poverty.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, Guangxi has used World Bank loans of 500 million
yuan to plant fast-growing trees on 170,000 ha. in 22 cities and
counties.
</P>
<P>
An official from the region's Frestry Department estimated that
Guangxi's forestry output value will surpass 13 billion yuan
within 20 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
