<HEADLINE> Ravanelli Signs For Marseille </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Italian striker Fabrizio
Ravanelli signed a four-year contract with French first division
club Olympique Marseille on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
His previous club Middlesbrough confirmed that the deal, worth
5.35 million pounds (8.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The news ended months of speculation which began when
Middlesbrough, beaten finalists in both the League Cup and the
F.A.Cup, were relegated from the English premier league at the
end of last season.
</P>
<P>
Ravanelli, who scored 31 goals for the club during the 1996-97
season after he transfered from Juventus, made it clear that he
did not wish to play for the club in a lower league. 
</P>
</TEXT>
