<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctors Bring Boy out of Coma with Acupuncture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at the No.1 Hospital
of Harbin Medical University have used acupuncture and blood
therapy to treat a five-year-old boy who had been in coma for 26
days.
</P>
<P>
The hospital is the first Chinese hospital to use the method to
treat a child in such a condition, which was the result of the
removal of part of the cerebral cortex.
</P>
<P>
The boy, Ning Jitan, from Heihe in Heilongjiang province, was
struck with viral encephalitis earlier this year and had
convulsions and a high fever, and lapsed into a coma.
</P>
<P>
When he was admitted to this hospital in the capital of
Heilongjiang, a pediatrician, Dr. Lin Shujing, decided to use
acupuncture and oxygen to treat the boy, and used a form of blood
treatment as an additional therapy.
</P>
<P>
The child's fever went away seven days later, and he was able
to sit up with help on the 21st day, and fully recovered within
two months. Tests showed that the boy's IQ was not affected by the
disease.
</P>
<P>
Doctors have used the method to treat a dozen children in
similar condition, with most of them recovering full physical and
mental health afterwards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
