<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay, U.S. Sign Anti-Drug Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, Septemer 25 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay and the United
States signed here today an agreement of cooperation on preventive
education and the war against production, processing, traffic and
consuming of drugs and connected activities.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Uruguay Antidrug National Board
secretary Alberto Scavarelli, and U.S. acting ambassador Nancy
Mason, on behalf of their respective governments.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government, as stated in the agreement, will supply
funds for a program for preventive education against the use
of drugs in Uruguay. This program is part of the agreement on
technical cooperation existing between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
The agreement foresees the extension of the sensibilization
program for some 1,500 teachers through seminars in which they
are trained to solve problems of drugs affecting students.
</P>
<P>
Funds will also be provided for the training of officials in
the National Naval Prefecture and other organization in charge of
law enforcement and the repression of drug trafficking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
