<HEADLINE> Indian Prime Minister Visits Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano
Prodi met visiting Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral here
today.
</P>
<P>
Prodi briefed his Indian guest on the progress in the European
monetary union and its role.
</P>
<P>
Gujral said that India is keenly watching the development of
the European monetary union and hoping to strengthen its relations
with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers also exchanged views on how to enhance
economic cooperation and cultural exchange between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Italian President Oscar Scalfaro also met
Gujral, who arrived here today for a one-day visit to Italy.
</P>
