<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills Three in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A traffic accident today
killed three and injured one.
</P>
<P>
A Toyota passenger vehicle collided today with a cargo truck
near the Santa Clara service station in the road to Guapiles,
east of San Jose.
</P>
<P>
According to police reports, the Toyota vehicle was going to
San Jose, the Costa Rican capital, while the cargo truck traveled
in the opposite direction, causing a head-on collision.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver was uninjured.
</P>
<P>
Police is investigating the details of the accident. 
</P>
