<HEADLINE> Hingis, Huber Advance at Leipzig Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis of Switzerland
and defending champion Anke Huber of Germany to move into the next
round with easy wins Thursday at the 450,000-U.S.-Dollar Leipzig
Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the world's top-ranked player, had little trouble
against Belgium's Sabine Appelmans and beat her opponent 6-3, 6-2
in the first quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Huber, who won the title in 1995 and 1996, climbed into the
quarter-finals with a 6-2, 6-3 win against Spain's Magui Serna and
set up a meeting against Croatia's Iva Majoli, the world's
fourth-ranked player.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's Amanda Coetzer, ranked sixth in the world, also
reached the quarter-finals with a 6-3, 7-5 win over Bulgaria's
Magdalena Malejeva, along with Sandra Kleinova. The Czech player
edged Indonesia's Yayuk Basuki, 4-6, 6-3, 7-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
