<HEADLINE> Rafter Advances to Semi-finals in Grand Slam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Rafter of Australia
trounced Chilean Marcelo Rios in straight sets 6-1, 7-6, reaching
the last four of the Grand Slam Cup in Munich on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The first set was a one-sided affair with Rafter taming Rios by
his wellknown serve-and-volley in just 27 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The second set was much tighter. Both players held serve until
a tie-break which Rafter took without conceding a point.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, who won the U.S. Open earlier this month, will meet
either Czech Petr Korda or Frenchman Cedric Pioline in the
semi-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
