<HEADLINE> China's freight Traffics Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- China's freight traffic
volume stood at 1.55 billion tons during the first seven months
this year, a mere drop of 0.4 percent from the same period in
1996, said the latest statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The freight traffic volume of railway and motor vehicles was
937 million tons and 252 million tons, respectively, down 0.7
percent and 1.7 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
That of civil aviation climbed to 684,000 tons, up 7.2
percent. 
</P>
