<HEADLINE> China's Passenger Traffic Volume up in January-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The passenger traffic volume
of China amounted to 2.94 billion persons during the first seven
months this year, up 2.5 percent over the same period in 1996,
according to the latest statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The railway and civil aviation sectors generated a passenger
traffic volume of 536 million persons and 32.13 million persons,
respectively, up 1.9 percent and three percent on the yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The passenger traffic volume of motor vehicles was 2.3 billion
persons, up three percent. 
</P>
