<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hotline on Poisoning Control Opened in Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang has opened China's
first hotline dealing with poisoning control.
</P>
<P>
Medical personnel manning the hotline answer questions related
to preventing and diagnosing suspected cases of poisoning,
according to the Poisoning Control and Counseling Center in
Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the center, jointly established by the Chinese
Medical University in Shenyang and the U.S.-based Chinese Medical
Board, is to enhance the general public's awareness of methods for
preventing poisoning and providing medical personnel with access
to related information.
</P>
<P>
Cases of food poisoning and other cases resulting from the
improper use of pesticides, pharmaceuticals and other dangerous
materials have been on the rise nationwide in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The center will also identify the composition of medicines and
chemicals, provide diagnostic services and sponsor
publicity campaigns.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
