<HEADLINE> Pak President Grieved over Loss of Lives in Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari has expressed deep grief over the death of about 30 people
in an ammunition shop explosion which occurred in northwestern
Pakistan Wednesday evening, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
In his condolence message, Leghari sympathized with the
bereaved families and directed the local administration to spare
no efforts in providing proper medical treatment to the injured,
said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at about 7:00 p.m. in Bajaur, around
80 kilometers northwest of Peshawar, capital of Pakistan's North
West Frontier Province.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 people were reportedly killed and dozens injured in
the blast.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion is yet unknown and investigations
are in progress, according to the sources.  
</P>
