<HEADLINE> Over 100 Greek Children Hurt by Swallowed Toys Each Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 children are
hurt by swallowed toys in Greece every year.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 117 children had been injured from swallowed toys
including chocolate eggs and junk food, said Dr. Eleni Petridou,
head of the Center for Prevention of Childhood Accidents.
</P>
<P>
He said that seven children were killed and 1,993 injured in
such accidents in the European Union countries this year. 
</P>
