<HEADLINE> Qian Reaffirms Supportive Policy of Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today reaffirmed China's policy
of supporting African countries in his talk with Bizima Karaha,
foreign minister of the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, Qian said that the traditional friendship
and prolonged exchanges between China and the Democratic Republic
of Congo can be traced back to the years when the African country
was striving for independence.
</P>
<P>
China likes to see the positive changes taken place in the
Democratic Republic of Congo and supports its stability and
development, according to the Chinese vice-premier.
</P>
<P>
He said the internal affairs of different countries should be
handled independently by the countries themselves. The external
world can offer help, but should not meddle about, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said China's consistent policy is to extend sympathy and
support, but no interference in the internal affairs of African
countries. He said he wishes that the Democratic Republic of Congo
will rebuild the country at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
Bizima said that the Chinese people have been providing great
help ever since the independence of his country. He reviewed
China's prolonged friendship towards the people of the Democratic
Republic of Congo, hoping that China will continue its help with
their efforts in realizing stability and restoration of economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
