<HEADLINE> 5 Security Council Permanent Members Back Annan's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministers
of the five permanent members of the U.N. Security Council today
reaffirmed their "strong support" for the world body and welcomed
the efforts by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan to improve its
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
They expressed their backing in a statement issued following a
meeting with Annan.
</P>
<P>
The statement particularly reaffirmed the commitment of the
five nations to achieving early and practical results in the
renewal of the largest world organization and its adaptation to
new world realities.
</P>
<P>
Reform is the major topic of the current session of the U.N.
General Assembly with a majority of the delegations voicing their
appreciations of and support for the reform package put forward by
Annan on July 16 this year.
</P>
<P>
The five ministers said that they support Annan's package and
are committed to participate "actively and constructively in a
considered debate" on Annan's proposals with a view to advancing
the reform in a timely manner in order to ensure highly quality,
effectiveness and better relevance of the U.N. activities."
</P>
<P>
On international peace and security, the statement stressed
the "primary responsibility" of the U.N. Security Council in
this respect.
</P>
<P>
"They reaffirmed that the Organization must further improve
its ability to act quickly and effectively to address threats to
international peace and security," the 18-point statement said.
</P>
</TEXT>
