<HEADLINE> Greece, Albania Sign Cooperation Protocols </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Albania today
signed three protocols to strengthen cooperation between their
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The protocols were signed by Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos and his Albanian counterpart, Sabit Brokaj, who
arrived here Wednesday for a three-day visit to Greece.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocols, the Greek military will assist Albania in
reorganizing its armed forces, training its army troops, and
providing Tirana with military supplies.
</P>
<P>
During their talks today, the two ministers also agreed on the
promotion of initiatives to secure peace and stability in the
region and the holding of regular meetings on all levels to
speedily carry out the agreements already signed between the two
countries. 
</P>
